<description>

A new savings account is created from the Client Detail page. The creation form contains Product Name dropdown (selecting a product auto-populates default values), Field Officer, Submitted On date, Nominal Annual Interest Rate, Interest Compounding Period, Interest Posting Period, Interest Calculated Using, Days in Year (all dropdowns, pre-filled from product), Minimum Opening Balance, Lock-in Period, Allow Overdraft checkbox, and a Charges section listing product charges with an option to add more. Clicking "Submit" creates the account in "Submitted and Pending Approval" status.

The Savings Account Detail page displays the account number, product name, client name, status badge, account balance, and available balance. Status badges include Submitted and Pending Approval, Approved, Active, Dormant, Closed, and Blocked. Action buttons change based on status: Pending offers Approve, Reject, and Withdraw Application; Approved offers Activate and Undo Approval; Active offers Deposit (form with Transaction Date, Transaction Amount, Payment Type — Cash, Check, Mobile Money — and payment detail fields; submitting credits the account), Withdraw (same form as Deposit — the system validates the withdrawal does not exceed available balance unless overdraft is enabled; if minimum balance is enforced and the withdrawal would breach it, an error is shown), Post Interest, Calculate Interest, Close, Block Account, Block Debit, and Block Credit. Tabs show Summary, Transactions (table of all deposits, withdrawals, and interest postings with Date, Type, Amount, and Running Balance), Charges, and Documents.

---


</description>

<workflows>
WF-001 | Create savings account (Submit form) | actor: <role> | branch: none | terminal: Submit | on_success: creates account in Submitted and Pending Approval
WF-002 | Approve a submitted account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Submitted and Pending Approval | terminal: Approve | on_success: changes status to Approved
WF-003 | Reject a submitted account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Submitted and Pending Approval | terminal: Reject | on_success: changes status to Rejected
WF-004 | Withdraw application for submitted account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Submitted and Pending Approval | terminal: Withdraw Application | on_success: withdraws the application
WF-005 | Activate an approved account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Approved | terminal: Activate | on_success: changes status to Active
WF-006 | Undo approval of an approved account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Approved | terminal: Undo Approval | on_success: reverts approval; changes status to Submitted and Pending Approval
WF-007 | Make a deposit to an active account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Deposit | on_success: credits the account
WF-008 | Make a withdrawal from an active account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Withdraw | on_success: creates withdrawal transaction and debits the account
WF-009 | Post interest to an active account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Post Interest | on_success: posts interest to the account
WF-010 | Calculate interest for an active account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Calculate Interest | on_success: calculates interest according to product settings
WF-011 | Close an active account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Close | on_success: changes status to Closed
WF-012 | Block an active account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Block Account | on_success: changes status to Blocked
WF-013 | Block debit on an active account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Block Debit | on_success: blocks debit transactions on the account
WF-014 | Block credit on an active account | actor: <role> | branch: entity_state == Active | terminal: Block Credit | on_success: blocks credit transactions on the account
</workflows>

